[MK] case called at 9:20am. 
Defendant Kimberly C. Zunker in court with Attorney Yelena Zarwell.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
ADA Shock verifies victim rights compliance. 
Service of the Amended Criminal Complaint admitted; reading is waived.
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of "No Contest" entered on Counts #, #2, #3, #4, #5 of the Amended Complaint; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the pleas, finds Ms. Zunker guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Counts #1, #2, #3, #4,#5 each, the Court withholds sentence, and places Ms. Zunker on Probation for three years, with conditions:
--to write a letter of apology to Lynn and Randall Grulke within thirty days; this is to be provided to the Agent for release to Mr. & Mrs. Grulke at the Agent's discretion
--no contact with Lynn Grulke or Randall Grulke, with the exception for writing the apology letter 
--Ms. Zunker shall undergo any mental health assessment as directed by the Agent, and follow through with recommended treatment
--to take all medications as prescribed by the treating physicians
--to undergo assessment, treatment, therapy and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--Ms. Zumker is shall have no possession or use of any financial transaction cards or account information that is not in her name
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as directed by the Agent
--to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 on each count ($2,215)

Days credit for time already served: 0 days
The Court denies the Defendant's request for expungement of these convictions.
